      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IRON WORKS (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 2 lengths at Cannington in a handy 42.05 beating King Kuna. One of the key runners again. TAKE MY ADVICE (2) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 652m behind Miss Envy (37.80) in a Free For All. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. HUM BUG MONELLI (4) rises 143m in distance at her first try over the longer trip. Comes here an impressive winner latest at Northam in Grade 5/6 in one of the quickest times of the program (29.50). Looks suited here and can measure up. CASHING OUT (5) can sneak into the finish.",
